ActRaiser Recomp  (@SNESBUILD_OS_NAME@/@SNESBUILD_ARCH_NAME@)
Version @SNESBUILD_VERSION@

This builds and runs the game on your computer from a game ROM you already
own. Everything needed is already in this folder. You do NOT need to install
anything.


WHAT YOU NEED
-------------
Your own game ROM: a ".sfc" file. Nothing else.


HOW TO PLAY  (two easy steps)
-----------------------------
1. Put your ROM (the ".sfc" file) into THIS folder, next to this README.

2. Start "@SNESBUILD_RUN_SCRIPT@":
      macOS    - double-click  run-build.command
      Windows  - double-click  run-build.bat
      Linux    - run           ./run-build.sh

   The first time takes a few minutes while it builds the game. When it
   finishes, the game starts on its own.

That's it. After the first build, a "run-game" file appears in this folder.
From then on, just start that to play right away - no waiting.


IF SOMETHING GOES WRONG
-----------------------
- "No ROM found": the ".sfc" file must be in this folder, next to this README.

- macOS says the file is from an unidentified developer: hold Control, click
  run-build.command, choose Open, then Open again. (You only do this once.)

- Linux says SDL2 is missing: install it with your package manager, e.g.
  "sudo apt install libsdl2-dev", then try again. (macOS and Windows already
  include it.)


OPTIONAL: YOUR OWN MUSIC AND HD GRAPHICS
----------------------------------------
This package plays the ROM's original music and graphics. If you want to add
your own, look in the "utils/game-assets" folder: "manifest.ini" lists every
music and graphic slot, and you drop matching files into the "audio" and "hd"
folders beside it. Anything you don't add simply stays original.


WHAT THE FOLDERS ARE
--------------------
- run-build.*     the button you press to build and play the first time.
- run-game.*      created after building; press it to play again instantly.
- utils/          the build tools and game files. You can ignore this.

Licensing and credits are in utils/LICENSE and utils/ATTRIBUTION.md.
